  "prompt": "What is the difference between angular velocity and angular acceleration?",
  "response": "Angular velocity and angular acceleration are two fundamental concepts in rotational kinematics that describe the motion of objects rotating about an axis. Here's a breakdown of their differences:\n\n### Angular Velocity (\u03c9)\n- **Definition**: Angular velocity is the rate at which an object rotates around an axis, describing how quickly the angular position changes with time.\n- **Formula**: \\( \\omega = \\frac{\\Delta \\theta}{\\Delta t} \\), where \\( \\Delta \\theta \\) is the change in angular position and \\( \\Delta t \\) is the change in time.\n- **Units**: Typically measured in **radians per second (rad/s)**.\n- **Direction**: It is a vector quantity, with its direction given by the **right-hand rule** (along the axis of rotation).\n- **Meaning**: It indicates how fast an object is spinning.\n\n### Angular Acceleration (\u03b1)\n- **Definition**: Angular acceleration is the rate at which angular velocity changes with time.\n- **Formula**: \\( \\alpha = \\frac{\\Delta \\omega}{\\Delta t} \\), where \\( \\Delta \\omega \\) is the change in angular velocity and \\( \\Delta t \\) is the change in time.\n- **Units**: Typically measured in **radians per second squared (rad/s\u00b2)**.\n- **Direction**: It is also a vector quantity, with its direction parallel to the change in angular velocity.\n- **Meaning**: It indicates whether an object's rotational speed is increasing, decreasing, or changing direction.\n\n### Key Differences:\n1. **Physical Meaning**:  \n   - Angular velocity describes **how fast** an object is rotating.  \n   - Angular acceleration describes **how quickly** the rotation is speeding up or slowing down.\n\n2. Relationship:  \n   - Angular acceleration is the **rate of change of angular velocity** over time.\n\n3. Units:  \n   - Angular velocity has units of **rad/s**.  \n   - Angular acceleration has units of **rad/s\u00b2**.\n\nIn summary, angular velocity tells you the speed of rotation, while angular acceleration tells you how that speed is changing.",
